        "description": {
            "name": "description",
            "type": "java.lang.String",
            "value": "Taking use of comments to escape JavaScript content is old and unnecessary.\r\nAll JavaScript-enabled browsers don't require the escaping of JavaScript (or any other language) inside of the <script> element.\r\n\r\nSo removing \"\/\/<!--\" and \"\/\/ -->\" wouldn't break any applications written with Zend Framework.\r\n\r\nHTML5 explicitly says <script> content is CDATA: \"The element does not represent content for the user.\" http:\/\/www.whatwg.org\/specs\/web-apps\/current-work\/#script"
